Package: networkformat
Type: Package
Title: Convert R Objects to Network Edgelists and Nodelists
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person(
      "Jesse", "Brandt",
      email = "jesseabrandt@users.noreply.github.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-7462-075X")
    )
Description: Converts R objects into network edgelist and nodelist format for
    visualization and analysis with packages like 'igraph', 'tidygraph', and
    'ggraph'. Works with atomic vectors (sequential edges), data frames
    (column-pair edges with tidyselect), and tree-based model objects
    ('randomForest', 'tree', 'rpart', 'xgboost', 'gbm'), and neural networks
    (Keras HDF5 and ONNX formats, extracting neuron-level weights and biases).
    Also provides one-step graph construction via as.igraph() and
    as_tbl_graph() methods.
